# Frontend (React) Conventions

## Role of the UI
The frontend is a **thin client** over the Go backend. No financial logic runs here. If you're tempted to compute a metric in JS — stop. Add a backend endpoint.

## Data Flow
- All numbers come from the backend, already computed and labeled with period.
- The UI renders: question → computed facts + LLM explanation + evidence chunks.
- Evidence chunks must be visibly attributable (source file + chunk id) — this is an auditable product.

## Components
- Functional components + hooks. No class components.
- Extract custom hooks for backend calls (`useAsk`, `useCompany`, `useUpload`).
- Colocate component + styles + tests.

## State
- Local state for UI concerns. Lift only when shared.
- No global store unless justified — this app is mostly request/response.

## Offline / On-Prem
- No third-party analytics, no Sentry, no Google Fonts CDN.
- Bundle all assets. Everything served from the same Docker image.
- No calls to anything but the local backend.

## Error UX
When the backend returns computed facts but the LLM explanation failed, still show the numbers. Never hide facts because prose is missing.

## Uploads
Uploads go straight to the backend. The UI does not parse documents — parsing is in `backend/internal/service/document_parser.go`.
